1
00:00:07,213 --> 00:00:10,088
I've had enough!
Leaks in Red Hook, leaks in City Hall.

2
00:00:10,755 --> 00:00:12,837
- You need to find them, Buck.
- [men grunting]

3
00:00:12,838 --> 00:00:14,130
Plug them.

4
00:00:14,588 --> 00:00:15,713
[gun fires]

5
00:00:16,880 --> 00:00:20,004
Whoever is leaking to the
City Without Fear site must be punished.

6
00:00:20,005 --> 00:00:22,837
Find out who it is, turn them over to me.

7
00:00:22,838 --> 00:00:24,962
[BB] It's my inside guy,
only he doesn't know it.

8
00:00:24,963 --> 00:00:27,796
[Daniel] If you are leaking stuff,
anything, stop.

9
00:00:27,797 --> 00:00:29,005
We could get hurt.

10
00:00:29,422 --> 00:00:32,171
[Karen] Vanessa killed Foggy
and nothing happened.

11
00:00:32,172 --> 00:00:33,547
[Matt] A line was crossed.

12
00:00:35,588 --> 00:00:38,171
Ever since Foggy died,
I didn't know who I was anymore.

13
00:00:38,172 --> 00:00:39,462
[Dex] What I did,

14
00:00:39,463 --> 00:00:41,421
what that woman had me do,

15
00:00:41,422 --> 00:00:43,088
I had to get my mind back.

16
00:00:43,755 --> 00:00:45,629
- One good deed.
- [men groan]

17
00:00:45,630 --> 00:00:47,838
- [Dex] It levels the scales again.
- [people screaming]

18
00:00:48,338 --> 00:00:50,380
[Daredevil grunts]

19
00:00:53,130 --> 00:00:54,838
[Vanessa] Wilson...

20
00:00:56,880 --> 00:00:58,797
[Fisk] Vanessa!

21
00:00:59,713 --> 00:01:01,505
[Vanessa breathing heavily]

22
00:01:08,130 --> 00:01:09,880
[♪ theme music playing]

23
00:02:56,713 --> 00:02:57,880
[waves lapping gently]

24
00:02:59,963 --> 00:03:01,422
[medical machines beeping]

25
00:03:08,630 --> 00:03:10,837
[doctor] I need blood pressure.
I need heart rate stat.

26
00:03:10,838 --> 00:03:12,337
- [Fisk] What's happening?
- Heart rate--

27
00:03:12,338 --> 00:03:13,462
- [Fisk] No, no, no.
- Sir, sir,

28
00:03:13,463 --> 00:03:15,254
- you cannot be in here right now.
- Get her!

29
00:03:15,255 --> 00:03:17,671
- Sir, you cannot be here.
- Vanessa. What is happening here?

30
00:03:17,672 --> 00:03:19,380
- Sir, sir.
- Vanessa!

31
00:03:20,380 --> 00:03:21,380
Vanessa...

32
00:03:23,588 --> 00:03:25,837
- [doctor] Sir, sir. Get back.
- [Fisk] Vanessa!

33
00:03:25,838 --> 00:03:29,379
[doctor] Sir, sir. Mr. Mayor,
I understand that you are anxious,

34
00:03:29,380 --> 00:03:32,296
and we will get you all the information
as soon as possible.

35
00:03:32,297 --> 00:03:34,587
- Can you...
- Yes, yes. Okay. Sir.

36
00:03:34,588 --> 00:03:36,212
- Sir, please.
- Sir, please.

37
00:03:36,213 --> 00:03:38,713
- Sir, please.
- Sir, let them do their job.

38
00:03:51,338 --> 00:03:52,587
[Sheila] All hands on deck.

39
00:03:52,588 --> 00:03:54,172
I need you to clear the schedule.

40
00:03:55,005 --> 00:03:57,879
- Yes! You need to...
- Like I said, absolutely no comment.

41
00:03:57,880 --> 00:03:59,879
How many times
do I have to tell you this, huh?

42
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:01,046
I'm not gonna have to... I don't know when

43
00:04:01,047 --> 00:04:02,838
- a statement's gonna be ready, all right?
- [Sheila] Yes. Yes, go.

44
00:04:05,838 --> 00:04:07,047
If you have them...

45
00:04:09,630 --> 00:04:10,755
keep them alive.

46
00:04:11,172 --> 00:04:12,463
Uh, we don't, sir.

47
00:04:12,922 --> 00:04:13,922
Not yet.

48
00:04:14,963 --> 00:04:16,672
Pretty sure we have them surrounded.

49
00:04:17,672 --> 00:04:19,797
Sir, I want to find them as bad as you do.

50
00:04:20,047 --> 00:04:21,047
No.

51
00:04:22,713 --> 00:04:23,713
You don't.

52
00:04:24,588 --> 00:04:25,672
You couldn't.

53
00:04:27,130 --> 00:04:29,172
Whatever you need, use it.

54
00:04:29,672 --> 00:04:30,672
You got it, sir.

55
00:04:32,338 --> 00:04:33,672
Officer Powell...

56
00:04:35,255 --> 00:04:36,255
Alive.

57
00:04:38,922 --> 00:04:39,922
Yeah.

58
00:04:45,463 --> 00:04:46,921
[officer 1] The tower is ready.
Have a seat.

59
00:04:46,922 --> 00:04:48,547
[officer 2] Let's move out.
Check that side.

60
00:04:56,755 --> 00:04:58,212
- Go, go, go, go, go!
- Over here.

61
00:04:58,213 --> 00:04:59,338
- Here, here.
- Let's go.

62
00:05:01,797 --> 00:05:05,130
- [panting, groaning]
- [staff chattering indistinctly]

63
00:05:07,088 --> 00:05:08,588
[Daredevil] Prep towels, where are they?

64
00:05:10,922 --> 00:05:13,172
- Now!
- Whatever you need, man. We're with you.

65
00:05:14,547 --> 00:05:16,379
You don't have to do this.

66
00:05:16,380 --> 00:05:17,504
- Hold still.
- This is balance.

67
00:05:17,505 --> 00:05:19,171
- You know it.
- Shut up.

68
00:05:19,172 --> 00:05:23,129
- [sirens echoing]
- [officer] Check in there. Check the door!

69
00:05:23,130 --> 00:05:25,422
- Do you have a boiler?
- Yeah, old shit back there.

70
00:05:26,463 --> 00:05:28,463
- Yeah, let's go.
- Leave me here.

71
00:05:28,963 --> 00:05:30,296
None of this matters now.

72
00:05:30,297 --> 00:05:31,672
- It matters to me.
- [grunts]

73
00:05:33,547 --> 00:05:34,879
Yeah, uh...

74
00:05:34,880 --> 00:05:36,297
No, no comment on that.

75
00:05:37,588 --> 00:05:39,880
I don't know when we're gonna have
a statement ready. No.

76
00:05:41,963 --> 00:05:42,963
Is she dead?

77
00:05:44,047 --> 00:05:46,921
What kind of sick
fucking question is that?

78
00:05:46,922 --> 00:05:49,504
- [sighs]
- [call ends]

79
00:05:49,505 --> 00:05:50,588
[phone chimes]

80
00:05:59,755 --> 00:06:02,755
[man on PA speaking indistinctly]

81
00:06:03,130 --> 00:06:04,546
How did you find me here?

82
00:06:04,547 --> 00:06:07,171
Seriously? I mean, how many hospitals
do you think there are, Daniel?

83
00:06:07,172 --> 00:06:09,212
- BB, you can't be here right now.
- Um...

84
00:06:09,213 --> 00:06:12,296
- Actually, technically, legally, I can.
- BB, think.

85
00:06:12,297 --> 00:06:14,088
Nobody can know where she is.
It's... It's...

86
00:06:14,963 --> 00:06:17,504
The mayor's not in a good place.
You gotta go.

87
00:06:17,505 --> 00:06:18,587
Okay.

88
00:06:18,588 --> 00:06:20,838
I-- I get it. I'll go, but just tell me.

89
00:06:22,005 --> 00:06:23,005
Is she alive?

90
00:06:24,547 --> 00:06:27,296
Look, there's a ton of chatter out there.
You have no idea.

91
00:06:27,297 --> 00:06:28,712
It's, like, crazy right now.

92
00:06:28,713 --> 00:06:31,005
And I just want to make sure
I get the story right.

93
00:06:33,713 --> 00:06:35,838
We're really fucking
doing this right now, huh?

94
00:06:41,713 --> 00:06:43,547
I... I'm so sorry.

95
00:06:45,130 --> 00:06:48,005
I shouldn't have come.
Just forget that I came, okay?

96
00:06:58,297 --> 00:07:00,047
She's in critical condition.

97
00:07:01,505 --> 00:07:03,838
They're... They're really lucky
to have you.

98
00:07:16,797 --> 00:07:17,797
[man] Mr. Fisk.

99
00:07:20,380 --> 00:07:21,380
Mr. Fisk.

100
00:07:24,922 --> 00:07:26,005
Arash Merati.

101
00:07:26,838 --> 00:07:28,087
Happy to meet you.

102
00:07:28,088 --> 00:07:29,172
Dr. Merati.

103
00:07:30,172 --> 00:07:32,587
Please understand that
I am here to do whatever I can

104
00:07:32,588 --> 00:07:34,047
- for your beloved wife.
- Yeah.

105
00:07:34,547 --> 00:07:36,505
I had a chance to look over her chart.

106
00:07:37,297 --> 00:07:40,129
She is, as you know,
in quite a precarious position.

107
00:07:40,130 --> 00:07:41,130
Yes.

108
00:07:41,630 --> 00:07:43,005
I've heard that you're...

109
00:07:43,797 --> 00:07:45,547
the top man in your field.

110
00:07:46,338 --> 00:07:49,297
Well nothing is certain where the mind
meets the soul, Mr. Fisk.

111
00:07:50,047 --> 00:07:53,171
But that said, I will do
everything in my power for her.

112
00:07:53,172 --> 00:07:54,213
Thank you.

113
00:08:03,463 --> 00:08:06,254
[woman] Knowing what a disaster
Verizon is in Chelsea,

114
00:08:06,255 --> 00:08:10,963
I can only imagine what sort of
cellular joy awaits me in central Vermont.

115
00:08:11,922 --> 00:08:15,130
- Hello.
- [woman speaking indistinctly]

116
00:08:30,422 --> 00:08:34,588
May I ask why you chose
not to include this piece tonight?

117
00:08:34,838 --> 00:08:37,421
I think it's pretty obvious
why I chose not to include it,

118
00:08:37,422 --> 00:08:40,963
but if you feel differently,
by all means, why should I put it up?

119
00:08:43,297 --> 00:08:44,297
[Vanessa] I don't know.

120
00:08:44,547 --> 00:08:46,380
There's just something about it.

121
00:08:49,588 --> 00:08:51,171
Do you understand

122
00:08:51,172 --> 00:08:52,962
what keeps us in business?

123
00:08:52,963 --> 00:08:56,713
What pays for the cute little
gray shoes that you're wearing?

124
00:08:59,297 --> 00:09:00,672
But I can tell you...

125
00:09:03,463 --> 00:09:07,338
that if the right person
walks through that door

126
00:09:08,297 --> 00:09:09,963
and sees this painting...

127
00:09:11,422 --> 00:09:13,796
sees his own deep, inexorable,

128
00:09:13,797 --> 00:09:17,672
miserable emptiness
reflected right back at him...

129
00:09:18,922 --> 00:09:20,462
I can promise you,

130
00:09:20,463 --> 00:09:22,922
you can add two zeros to the list price,

131
00:09:23,672 --> 00:09:27,838
and it'll sell faster
than any other piece out front.

132
00:09:29,505 --> 00:09:31,213
The piece stays right where it is.

133
00:09:31,713 --> 00:09:34,338
- [footsteps retreating]
- Your call.

134
00:09:45,672 --> 00:09:47,046
[Dex] I'm bleeding out.

135
00:09:47,047 --> 00:09:48,754
I've seen it enough times to know.

136
00:09:48,755 --> 00:09:50,505
[Daredevil] I'm not interested
in your opinion.

137
00:09:51,713 --> 00:09:52,963
I've earned this...

138
00:09:54,005 --> 00:09:56,380
many times over. It's okay.

139
00:09:59,172 --> 00:10:00,337
[grunts]

140
00:10:00,338 --> 00:10:01,713
[breathing raggedly]

141
00:10:03,922 --> 00:10:05,172
You think she's dead?

142
00:10:07,213 --> 00:10:08,213
I don't know.

143
00:10:09,797 --> 00:10:10,797
Come on.

144
00:10:12,088 --> 00:10:14,172
And if she is, it all balances.

145
00:10:15,755 --> 00:10:17,672
Your friend, Fisk's wife.

146
00:10:18,755 --> 00:10:21,297
Scales settled.

147
00:10:22,338 --> 00:10:24,838
- And I'm ready for judgment.
- Oh, good for you.

148
00:10:25,922 --> 00:10:27,172
You're not listening.

149
00:10:29,255 --> 00:10:32,505
That night you threw me off the roof,
I was supposed to die.

150
00:10:33,005 --> 00:10:35,255
Four-story. No one survives that.

151
00:10:35,922 --> 00:10:36,922
And yet...

152
00:10:37,755 --> 00:10:39,422
Maybe that's the grand design.

153
00:10:41,213 --> 00:10:42,213
You're getting it.

154
00:10:43,422 --> 00:10:44,630
No, I'm not getting it.

155
00:10:46,005 --> 00:10:48,088
If she's dead. Vanessa.

156
00:10:49,213 --> 00:10:50,379
That's just murder.

157
00:10:50,380 --> 00:10:52,046
Vanessa, Foggy--

158
00:10:52,047 --> 00:10:53,755
[choking]

159
00:10:58,463 --> 00:10:59,505
Don't say his name.

160
00:11:01,797 --> 00:11:04,088
You don't get to say his name.
Do you understand?

161
00:11:05,547 --> 00:11:09,296
- You-- [groans]
- Tell me you understand.

162
00:11:09,297 --> 00:11:10,422
Don't say his name.

163
00:11:13,713 --> 00:11:16,296
[Foggy] Even the best avocados
have to do grunt work.

164
00:11:16,297 --> 00:11:18,754
[Matt] I guess we're gonna have to
break it to Josie that we're not

165
00:11:18,755 --> 00:11:21,213
- paying off the tab tonight.
- She'll understand.

166
00:11:21,672 --> 00:11:25,379
Lionel McCoy, 29 years old,
possession of multiple narcotics,

167
00:11:25,380 --> 00:11:27,254
including, but not limited to,

168
00:11:27,255 --> 00:11:29,504
Oxy, Moxy, Roxy,

169
00:11:29,505 --> 00:11:31,254
and wait for it, Xoxy.

170
00:11:31,255 --> 00:11:33,337
[chuckles] Christ,
guy's a walking pharmacy.

171
00:11:33,338 --> 00:11:36,296
Throw in a firearms charge, fake ID,

172
00:11:36,297 --> 00:11:38,588
intent to distribute,
obstruction of justice.

173
00:11:39,588 --> 00:11:41,962
Some yada. A little more yada
and yet another yada.

174
00:11:41,963 --> 00:11:43,671
And this guy is looking down the barrel--

175
00:11:43,672 --> 00:11:45,588
Wait, wait, wait. Okay, hold on.
Let me guess.

176
00:11:46,297 --> 00:11:48,505
I want to say 12 to 15.

177
00:11:49,255 --> 00:11:50,546
I'm sorry, Mr. Murdock.

178
00:11:50,547 --> 00:11:52,962
- The answer is actually 10 to 12.
- Oh, come on.

179
00:11:52,963 --> 00:11:54,921
- I was so close.
- But thank you for playing with us.

180
00:11:54,922 --> 00:11:56,671
And we do hope you enjoyed your stay

181
00:11:56,672 --> 00:11:59,296
- in the correctional facility.
- [chuckles]

182
00:11:59,297 --> 00:12:01,337
Okay, what do you say?
Uh, we ask for six to eight,

183
00:12:01,338 --> 00:12:02,962
he's out in five for good behavior.

184
00:12:02,963 --> 00:12:06,921
Yep. Levine wants him to plead out,
so we take the best offer on the table.

185
00:12:06,922 --> 00:12:09,837
Under no circumstances
does this go to trial.

186
00:12:09,838 --> 00:12:10,921
Heard.

187
00:12:10,922 --> 00:12:12,046
After you, Counselor.

188
00:12:12,047 --> 00:12:13,588
Why, thank you, Counselor.

189
00:12:17,713 --> 00:12:20,837
Good afternoon, Mr. McCoy.
My name is Matthew Murdock.

190
00:12:20,838 --> 00:12:22,838
- This is my associate--
- Foggy the Fembot?

191
00:12:25,088 --> 00:12:26,379
Ray?

192
00:12:26,380 --> 00:12:28,337
[chuckles] You-- You know each other?

193
00:12:28,338 --> 00:12:30,712
Guy upstairs got a sick
sense of humor, don't he?

194
00:12:30,713 --> 00:12:32,172
We, um...

195
00:12:33,838 --> 00:12:35,713
grew up in the same building.

196
00:12:36,713 --> 00:12:38,171
Isn't your name Ray?

197
00:12:38,172 --> 00:12:40,922
[Lionel] What, you think I'd go by Lionel
in that neighborhood?

198
00:12:41,463 --> 00:12:43,797
You know, Fembot,
he used to clean my sneakers.

199
00:12:44,838 --> 00:12:46,629
- Didn't you?
- Maybe we could refrain

200
00:12:46,630 --> 00:12:48,129
from the name-calling, Mr. McCoy?

201
00:12:48,130 --> 00:12:50,212
- What's with him? You blind or something?
- [Foggy] How--

202
00:12:50,213 --> 00:12:52,254
How's, um, Connor?

203
00:12:52,255 --> 00:12:54,088
He moved upstate last year.

204
00:12:54,755 --> 00:12:55,963
Oneonta.

205
00:12:56,630 --> 00:12:58,962
I don't know.
Last I heard he was doing roofs.

206
00:12:58,963 --> 00:13:01,255
Some shit like that.
Gutters, maybe. I don't know.

207
00:13:01,672 --> 00:13:03,463
Knocked up the first chick he could.

208
00:13:04,505 --> 00:13:06,379
Okay, maybe we should, uh...

209
00:13:06,380 --> 00:13:08,172
Oh, yeah, please.

210
00:13:09,338 --> 00:13:12,671
We, uh, used to... hang out.

211
00:13:12,672 --> 00:13:14,587
Me and his brother, I mean.

212
00:13:14,588 --> 00:13:15,879
We were best friends.

213
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:18,297
- The aforementioned Connor.
- Mmm-hmm.

214
00:13:18,713 --> 00:13:21,254
All right, uh, Mr. McCoy,
you're facing a laundry list

215
00:13:21,255 --> 00:13:22,754
- of state charges. I suggest--
- It's all bullshit.

216
00:13:22,755 --> 00:13:24,837
Regardless,
our firm was retained to represent you,

217
00:13:24,838 --> 00:13:27,130
- and Mr. Nelson and I would like--
- [Lionel snickers]

218
00:13:28,047 --> 00:13:29,047
You Mr. Nelson?

219
00:13:29,838 --> 00:13:31,797
- Is that supposed to be you?
- Foggy?

220
00:13:32,630 --> 00:13:35,296
You wanna tell your friend here what
the firm's professional advice would be?

221
00:13:35,297 --> 00:13:37,297
- Yeah, yeah. Go ahead, Mr. Nelson.
- [clears throat]

222
00:13:38,047 --> 00:13:39,047
What do you got?

223
00:13:40,213 --> 00:13:42,838
Right. Well, we, um...

224
00:13:44,505 --> 00:13:46,754
Given the charges,
the evidence against you,

225
00:13:46,755 --> 00:13:49,547
we suggest that you take a plea deal.

226
00:13:51,172 --> 00:13:53,421
We ask for a reduction in sentencing.

227
00:13:53,422 --> 00:13:55,463
And best case scenario, you're out in...

228
00:13:56,005 --> 00:13:59,087
- five to six.
- Or three to four with exemplary behavior.

229
00:13:59,088 --> 00:14:01,087
- [Lionel] Oh, five to six.
- Three to four if you...

230
00:14:01,088 --> 00:14:02,796
If, if, if, if, if I what?

231
00:14:02,797 --> 00:14:04,422
If I-- If I find God?

232
00:14:05,338 --> 00:14:07,796
Huh? If I-- If I mop the john?
Wait the library?

233
00:14:07,797 --> 00:14:09,921
I believe they call it rehabilitation,
Mr. McCoy.

234
00:14:09,922 --> 00:14:11,172
Mmm-hmm. You don't understand.

235
00:14:11,755 --> 00:14:14,005
The guys I work with want me dead.

236
00:14:15,005 --> 00:14:17,921
I mean, that's the whole reason
you two are even here in the first place.

237
00:14:17,922 --> 00:14:19,046
Cop a deal,

238
00:14:19,047 --> 00:14:20,338
they told you, right?

239
00:14:21,088 --> 00:14:23,797
No trial. Huh?

240
00:14:24,505 --> 00:14:25,630
You want to know why?

241
00:14:26,380 --> 00:14:30,796
Because they got about ten guys
on the inside just waiting to take me out.

242
00:14:30,797 --> 00:14:32,337
All right? That's how this ends.

243
00:14:32,338 --> 00:14:34,921
That's how this goes.
All right? So, it's not three to four,

244
00:14:34,922 --> 00:14:37,296
it's not six to eight
if I'm a little good boy. All right?

245
00:14:37,297 --> 00:14:39,672
It's 24 hours, counselor.

246
00:14:40,255 --> 00:14:42,672
I'm a dead man the second I go in.

247
00:14:43,380 --> 00:14:44,422
So...

248
00:14:46,255 --> 00:14:47,713
I'm not signing shit.

249
00:14:49,172 --> 00:14:51,212
I'll take my chances
with a public defender.

250
00:14:51,213 --> 00:14:53,296
All right. Take it easy.
Back-- Back up here.

251
00:14:53,297 --> 00:14:55,547
What-- [sighs] What are you talking about?

252
00:14:57,130 --> 00:14:59,463
You two don't even know
who you work for, do you?

253
00:15:06,797 --> 00:15:08,922
[cell phone buzzing]

254
00:15:10,713 --> 00:15:11,838
This is Wesley.

255
00:15:14,463 --> 00:15:15,463
Right.

256
00:15:17,255 --> 00:15:18,255
I'll let you know.

257
00:15:22,547 --> 00:15:25,047
We may have an issue with the Lion.

258
00:15:30,005 --> 00:15:31,797
Are you familiar with Bitcoin?

259
00:15:33,880 --> 00:15:35,297
In light of the Russians...

260
00:15:38,255 --> 00:15:40,380
we should start diversifying.

261
00:15:42,338 --> 00:15:44,463
In this new world...

262
00:15:46,838 --> 00:15:50,963
we can no longer be old-fashioned
in our way of thinking.

263
00:15:52,255 --> 00:15:54,837
I do have some contacts
in the crypto space,

264
00:15:54,838 --> 00:15:56,629
but if I may, I would suggest

265
00:15:56,630 --> 00:15:59,672
it might be too volatile

266
00:16:00,255 --> 00:16:01,379
for our needs, sir.

267
00:16:01,380 --> 00:16:05,505
Hmm. Now, perhaps you have other ideas.

268
00:16:06,755 --> 00:16:08,047
Come to think of it,

269
00:16:08,338 --> 00:16:11,838
I have a friend who runs an art gallery.

270
00:16:13,422 --> 00:16:16,338
Blue chip. Real money.

271
00:16:17,547 --> 00:16:19,630
It could be an interesting market for us.

272
00:16:21,630 --> 00:16:22,838
The art world.

273
00:16:23,797 --> 00:16:24,838
Pretension.

274
00:16:26,172 --> 00:16:30,005
And airs of posing as something...

275
00:16:31,505 --> 00:16:32,838
meaningful.

276
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:36,463
[medical machine beeping slowly]

277
00:16:59,255 --> 00:17:00,379
[Daredevil] Keep moving.

278
00:17:00,380 --> 00:17:01,588
We need to get you help.

279
00:17:02,505 --> 00:17:04,712
- [groans]
- No, no, no. No!

280
00:17:04,713 --> 00:17:06,212
No, no! Come on.

281
00:17:06,213 --> 00:17:07,879
- [wheezing]
- Stop it.

282
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:10,797
- Stop! [grunts angrily]
- [Daredevil screams]

283
00:17:11,588 --> 00:17:14,712
[sighs] This is pointless.

284
00:17:14,713 --> 00:17:16,047
Let's be real.

285
00:17:16,672 --> 00:17:18,213
You're not gonna mourn me.

286
00:17:19,338 --> 00:17:20,338
Go on, get up.

287
00:17:21,505 --> 00:17:23,879
- You need help. Let's go.
- Mmm-mmm.

288
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:26,337
- [Daredevil] Come on.
- Get your fucking hands off me!

289
00:17:26,338 --> 00:17:29,005
- [Daredevil] Come on!
- [groaning]

290
00:17:32,547 --> 00:17:34,380
[Dex] First, you try to kill me,

291
00:17:34,922 --> 00:17:36,797
and then you try to save me,

292
00:17:38,047 --> 00:17:41,547
and I'm the one who needs help? [chuckles]

293
00:17:44,463 --> 00:17:47,088
I'm trying to save you
because I tried to kill you.

294
00:17:48,755 --> 00:17:50,547
I lost sight of that on Josie's roof.

295
00:17:52,630 --> 00:17:54,588
Maybe tonight's penance is mutual.

296
00:17:57,130 --> 00:17:58,130
Come on.

297
00:17:58,838 --> 00:18:01,505
- Come on.
- [grunting]

298
00:18:06,088 --> 00:18:08,130
[grunting]

299
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:10,004
You said Henderson?

300
00:18:10,005 --> 00:18:11,672
- Hernandez.
- [Matt] Oh, damn.

301
00:18:13,797 --> 00:18:16,337
All right. Punching out
before the elevator rush.

302
00:18:16,338 --> 00:18:17,505
Have you got plans?

303
00:18:18,838 --> 00:18:19,921
Allowance?

304
00:18:19,922 --> 00:18:21,005
[Matt] Oh, that's right.

305
00:18:21,963 --> 00:18:23,588
What are we, uh... What are we up to?

306
00:18:24,713 --> 00:18:27,962
Seventeen-hundred even as of tonight.

307
00:18:27,963 --> 00:18:31,129
[whistles] What do you think?
Eighteen more months

308
00:18:31,130 --> 00:18:33,421
before we open doors
on Murdock and Nelson?

309
00:18:33,422 --> 00:18:35,005
[Jeff] Congratulations, fuckos.

310
00:18:35,672 --> 00:18:37,379
Great job at the precinct today.

311
00:18:37,380 --> 00:18:39,296
All you had to do
was have the guy sign his name.

312
00:18:39,297 --> 00:18:40,796
Didn't even have to be legible.

313
00:18:40,797 --> 00:18:42,880
Plead out, sign the papers, move on.

314
00:18:43,588 --> 00:18:45,129
- But, no.
- Jeff, we...

315
00:18:45,130 --> 00:18:47,422
I'm sorry. Did you mean "Mr. Levine"?

316
00:18:48,213 --> 00:18:50,337
Right, yes. Sorry.

317
00:18:50,338 --> 00:18:51,922
- Mr. Levine, we--
- Guess what?

318
00:18:52,338 --> 00:18:53,338
I don't care.

319
00:18:53,963 --> 00:18:55,838
It's the public defender's problem now,
isn't it?

320
00:18:56,630 --> 00:18:58,879
Unfortunately, they need all these papers,

321
00:18:58,880 --> 00:19:01,463
collated and delivered to their office
by Monday morning.

322
00:19:02,463 --> 00:19:04,005
Happy Fraturday, fucknuts.

323
00:19:06,338 --> 00:19:07,421
Have a nice weekend.

324
00:19:07,422 --> 00:19:08,505
[chuckles]

325
00:19:10,255 --> 00:19:12,046
[Matt] He's definitely into
something weird.

326
00:19:12,047 --> 00:19:13,880
Totally. Like feet.

327
00:19:14,713 --> 00:19:16,047
[chuckles] What's wrong with feet?

328
00:19:16,422 --> 00:19:18,129
Nothing. I'm just saying that

329
00:19:18,130 --> 00:19:19,504
I can imagine Mr. Levine

330
00:19:19,505 --> 00:19:21,837
doing some weird shit with feet.
That's all.

331
00:19:21,838 --> 00:19:22,838
[Matt] Gross.

332
00:19:25,047 --> 00:19:26,712
Exhibit C, column two.

333
00:19:26,713 --> 00:19:28,297
Column two, exhibit C.

334
00:19:30,005 --> 00:19:31,338
Just, uh, for the record,

335
00:19:31,797 --> 00:19:33,796
I don't have a problem with feet.

336
00:19:33,797 --> 00:19:35,754
You're also not not weird, so...

337
00:19:35,755 --> 00:19:36,755
[chuckles]

338
00:19:38,588 --> 00:19:39,588
Whoa.

339
00:19:40,922 --> 00:19:41,922
What?

340
00:19:42,255 --> 00:19:43,337
The warrant.

341
00:19:43,338 --> 00:19:47,005
The address on the warrant they used
to access his apartment, it's wrong.

342
00:19:47,547 --> 00:19:50,963
It says 536 West 49th Street,
apartment 5E.

343
00:19:51,588 --> 00:19:52,712
That isn't correct?

344
00:19:52,713 --> 00:19:54,338
It's 536 1/2.

345
00:19:54,713 --> 00:19:57,296
That's where he lived.
The McCoys, I mean, that was our address.

346
00:19:57,297 --> 00:19:59,463
536 1/2 West 49th.

347
00:20:01,088 --> 00:20:02,587
No, that-- That can't be right.

348
00:20:02,588 --> 00:20:03,838
It is right.

349
00:20:04,922 --> 00:20:06,963
I mean, it's a clerical error, but...

350
00:20:08,630 --> 00:20:09,755
this is invalid.

351
00:20:10,755 --> 00:20:14,379
Everything discovered in this warrant
is fruit of the poison tree.

352
00:20:14,380 --> 00:20:15,380
It's inadmissible.

353
00:20:16,922 --> 00:20:19,047
Which means that piece of paper is...

354
00:20:19,672 --> 00:20:21,338
Get-out-of-jail free card.

355
00:20:25,755 --> 00:20:26,755
What do we do?

356
00:20:30,338 --> 00:20:32,921
Oh, come on, Foggy.
It's not like he deserves to walk.

357
00:20:32,922 --> 00:20:35,087
I don't recall the word "deserve"

358
00:20:35,088 --> 00:20:36,380
coming up in law school.

359
00:20:36,713 --> 00:20:38,796
He's in bed with the mob,
he's selling drugs,

360
00:20:38,797 --> 00:20:40,421
he's poisoning the neighborhood.

361
00:20:40,422 --> 00:20:41,755
[Foggy] Yeah, but...

362
00:20:42,255 --> 00:20:45,379
But what? He was also a raging prick
to you when you were kids?

363
00:20:45,380 --> 00:20:48,212
You want to spring the guy
who calls you Foggy the Fembot?

364
00:20:48,213 --> 00:20:50,297
[scoffs] No, I don't.

365
00:20:51,297 --> 00:20:52,297
But, Matt...

366
00:20:52,755 --> 00:20:54,129
we are his attorneys.

367
00:20:54,130 --> 00:20:56,629
- We're associates.
- Don't get technical.

368
00:20:56,630 --> 00:20:58,879
- Either way, Jeff made it sound like--
- Mr. Levine.

369
00:20:58,880 --> 00:21:00,504
- Thank you.
- [chuckles] Okay, okay, fine.

370
00:21:00,505 --> 00:21:03,296
Dark Lord of Unspoken Kink Levine

371
00:21:03,297 --> 00:21:05,504
made it sound like
we're not only off the case,

372
00:21:05,505 --> 00:21:07,463
but our badges might not work on Monday.

373
00:21:08,338 --> 00:21:09,672
Ray, Lionel...

374
00:21:10,130 --> 00:21:11,712
he had a hard life, Matt.

375
00:21:11,713 --> 00:21:13,546
[sarcastically] Aw! Cue the violin.

376
00:21:13,547 --> 00:21:16,254
His dad, he was not a good guy.

377
00:21:16,255 --> 00:21:18,046
And their mom, Suzanne, she drank.

378
00:21:18,047 --> 00:21:20,712
A lot. She died when we were
in the eighth grade.

379
00:21:20,713 --> 00:21:21,796
Okay?

380
00:21:21,797 --> 00:21:24,005
Cirrhosis, liver failure.

381
00:21:24,213 --> 00:21:26,379
- [Matt sighs]
- He never had a chance.

382
00:21:26,380 --> 00:21:28,338
His brother did though, didn't he?
What was his name? Connor?

383
00:21:28,755 --> 00:21:30,338
Connor was younger.

384
00:21:30,588 --> 00:21:32,212
Lionel took the brunt of it.

385
00:21:32,213 --> 00:21:34,921
- I didn't like him.
- And you want to let him out

386
00:21:34,922 --> 00:21:37,922
to continue to do horrendous things
to a whole bunch of new people.

387
00:21:38,672 --> 00:21:41,087
- I want to do the right thing.
- I don't know, Foggy.

388
00:21:41,088 --> 00:21:42,088
I don't know.

389
00:21:43,463 --> 00:21:46,129
You sell drugs, you're trafficking
firearms, you get caught.

390
00:21:46,130 --> 00:21:47,796
I'm sorry. There are consequences.

391
00:21:47,797 --> 00:21:50,671
His crew, whoever he was working with,

392
00:21:50,672 --> 00:21:52,921
they're gonna kill him when he's inside.

393
00:21:52,922 --> 00:21:55,212
Yeah, that might be
the definition of consequences.

394
00:21:55,213 --> 00:21:57,254
But does the punishment fit the crime?

395
00:21:57,255 --> 00:21:59,587
- Crimes past, present or future?
- So you think we should ignore it?

396
00:21:59,588 --> 00:22:01,587
- Ignore what?
- It's our job

397
00:22:01,588 --> 00:22:02,962
to represent our clients

398
00:22:02,963 --> 00:22:05,629
to the best of our abilities.
Suppressing evidence--

399
00:22:05,630 --> 00:22:07,712
Objection. "Suppressing" is questionable.

400
00:22:07,713 --> 00:22:10,671
One might even say inflammatory phrasing
in this particular instance, Counselor.

401
00:22:10,672 --> 00:22:12,671
Aren't you supposed to be
the Catholic one here?

402
00:22:12,672 --> 00:22:15,713
Oh, come on. All right, so, fine,
you want to go with guilt now?

403
00:22:20,047 --> 00:22:21,463
How about mercy?

404
00:22:22,713 --> 00:22:25,213
There's got to be something
about that in the Bible.

405
00:22:26,172 --> 00:22:27,505
Second chances,

406
00:22:28,047 --> 00:22:29,088
redemption?

407
00:22:30,755 --> 00:22:33,797
All I know is if he goes to jail, he dies.

408
00:22:34,838 --> 00:22:38,380
And all I know is that
might not be our problem.

409
00:22:38,963 --> 00:22:40,505
Unfortunately...

410
00:22:41,547 --> 00:22:42,588
it is now.

411
00:22:45,630 --> 00:22:46,796
[cell phone buzzes]

412
00:22:46,797 --> 00:22:47,797
This is Wesley.

413
00:22:48,130 --> 00:22:49,671
That's great to hear.

414
00:22:49,672 --> 00:22:51,630
Let me talk to him. I'll call you back.

415
00:22:53,047 --> 00:22:54,630
I take it he's available?

416
00:22:55,422 --> 00:22:57,338
He's here for a couple of weeks, just...

417
00:22:58,088 --> 00:22:59,296
moving through town.

418
00:22:59,297 --> 00:23:01,088
He's good. Very good.

419
00:23:01,963 --> 00:23:03,005
Maybe the best.

420
00:23:04,672 --> 00:23:05,672
Use him.

421
00:23:06,880 --> 00:23:08,630
- [cell phone beeps]
- We're a go.

422
00:23:12,463 --> 00:23:14,712
[anchor] His approval ratings
suggest otherwise.

423
00:23:14,713 --> 00:23:16,046
[reporter] Good afternoon, Brian.

424
00:23:16,047 --> 00:23:18,379
Breaking news, just in to New York One.

425
00:23:18,380 --> 00:23:21,671
I am standing just outside
the entrance to Metro General Hospital.

426
00:23:21,672 --> 00:23:24,087
here on Fifth Avenue, where we understand

427
00:23:24,088 --> 00:23:26,504
Vanessa Fisk is in critical condition.

428
00:23:26,505 --> 00:23:28,337
Fucking BB, no way.

429
00:23:28,338 --> 00:23:30,421
[reporter] ...in last night's
violent attack on...

430
00:23:30,422 --> 00:23:31,504
- Mr. Blake.
- No way.

431
00:23:31,505 --> 00:23:32,962
- Can I get an update on Mrs. Fisk?
- No way. No.

432
00:23:32,963 --> 00:23:35,504
- Can you do me a favor and fuck off?
- And who the hell are you?

433
00:23:35,505 --> 00:23:37,505
I'm the one telling you
to fuck off. Keep up.

434
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:39,380
Do I need to call the Task Force?

435
00:23:43,672 --> 00:23:45,005
They're horrible. Trust me.

436
00:23:50,255 --> 00:23:51,297
Thanks for that.

437
00:23:53,588 --> 00:23:54,588
[sighs]

438
00:23:55,963 --> 00:23:57,046
Tough day.

439
00:23:57,047 --> 00:23:58,047
The worst.

440
00:23:59,172 --> 00:24:00,797
Buck, where were you last night?

441
00:24:01,588 --> 00:24:02,755
I had to run an errand.

442
00:24:03,672 --> 00:24:05,130
- How is he?
- Better.

443
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:07,212
She's out of surgery.

444
00:24:07,213 --> 00:24:09,671
It's too soon to tell,
but it's not bad news so far.

445
00:24:09,672 --> 00:24:11,005
- Thank Christ.
- Mmm-hmm.

446
00:24:12,755 --> 00:24:14,463
You know, I could kill for a hot dog.

447
00:24:16,213 --> 00:24:17,422
Yeah, sure.

448
00:24:17,880 --> 00:24:18,880
Come on.

449
00:24:21,672 --> 00:24:22,672
[Fisk] It's done.

450
00:24:23,213 --> 00:24:24,337
[Dr. Merati] Yes.

451
00:24:24,338 --> 00:24:25,338
Yes, indeed.

452
00:24:26,172 --> 00:24:27,463
The surgery went quite well.

453
00:24:28,838 --> 00:24:29,963
Tell me everything.

454
00:24:30,755 --> 00:24:34,004
[Dr. Merati] Well, the procedure was long,
as you know, and quite involved.

455
00:24:34,005 --> 00:24:35,005
But...

456
00:24:35,422 --> 00:24:37,338
I'm optimistic in nature.

457
00:24:37,838 --> 00:24:38,963
And I remain hopeful.

458
00:24:40,380 --> 00:24:41,380
Hope?

459
00:24:44,713 --> 00:24:46,338
She's gonna be fine.

460
00:24:50,838 --> 00:24:52,587
[Vanessa] Please lean it against the wall.

461
00:24:52,588 --> 00:24:54,255
I'll deal with it later.

462
00:24:55,505 --> 00:24:56,713
[exhales]

463
00:24:58,838 --> 00:25:01,254
So, same spot, different piece?

464
00:25:01,255 --> 00:25:02,297
Mmm-hmm.

465
00:25:03,713 --> 00:25:05,547
I hope you know what you're doing.

466
00:25:18,797 --> 00:25:20,172
[waves lapping shore]

467
00:25:23,255 --> 00:25:24,588
[♪ melancholy music playing]

468
00:25:54,130 --> 00:25:57,379
You know, there's hot dog carts
on every corner.

469
00:25:57,380 --> 00:25:59,254
[Buck] Yeah,
I thought we might take a drive.

470
00:25:59,255 --> 00:26:00,421
Have a little chat.

471
00:26:00,422 --> 00:26:01,629
A chat?

472
00:26:01,630 --> 00:26:03,546
Buck, Fisk needs me.

473
00:26:03,547 --> 00:26:05,962
The man is aware we're going to Albany.

474
00:26:05,963 --> 00:26:07,963
Yo, Albany?

475
00:26:09,422 --> 00:26:11,380
Dude, you didn't say
anything about Albany.

476
00:26:13,672 --> 00:26:16,672
The other day in your office,
you were asking about my background.

477
00:26:17,047 --> 00:26:19,047
- Yeah, sure.
- Well, you were right.

478
00:26:19,672 --> 00:26:20,838
I was Regiment 22.

479
00:26:23,963 --> 00:26:27,463
When you were reading about my past,
did you see anything about Helmand?

480
00:26:28,797 --> 00:26:29,797
The mayonnaise?

481
00:26:31,338 --> 00:26:33,047
No, Daniel, not the mayonnaise.

482
00:26:33,630 --> 00:26:34,672
Afghanistan.

483
00:26:36,172 --> 00:26:40,212
My squadron, and I imagine many others,
were tasked with night raids,

484
00:26:40,213 --> 00:26:43,547
that no man of fighting age
would survive the night.

485
00:26:44,380 --> 00:26:47,046
But it was opium farmers, not insurgents.

486
00:26:47,047 --> 00:26:49,755
Apparently, Her Majesty
considered 14 fighting age.

487
00:26:52,588 --> 00:26:54,213
Jesus Christ, what did you do?

488
00:26:57,047 --> 00:26:58,172
What I was ordered to.

489
00:26:59,963 --> 00:27:00,963
That's my point.

490
00:27:02,838 --> 00:27:05,171
There are pivotal moments
in a man's life, Daniel,

491
00:27:05,172 --> 00:27:08,297
which define what kind of man he is,

492
00:27:08,797 --> 00:27:09,963
what he's really made of.

493
00:27:10,463 --> 00:27:13,005
Mr. Fisk changed my life
in one of those moments.

494
00:27:13,630 --> 00:27:15,088
I imagine you can relate, right?

495
00:27:16,297 --> 00:27:18,172
Staten Island to City Hall.

496
00:27:18,630 --> 00:27:20,088
Head of communications.

497
00:27:20,838 --> 00:27:22,422
That's quite a trajectory.

498
00:27:24,338 --> 00:27:25,797
That's impressive, Daniel.

499
00:27:27,630 --> 00:27:28,796
Appreciate that.

500
00:27:28,797 --> 00:27:30,797
My God, it has not been easy, has it?

501
00:27:31,422 --> 00:27:33,880
Muse, The Northern Star leak.

502
00:27:35,047 --> 00:27:38,755
And now it seems someone, God knows who,
has leaked the hospital to the press.

503
00:27:42,213 --> 00:27:44,297
What? You're not saying you think it's me,
are you?

504
00:27:45,755 --> 00:27:47,963
Buck, I didn't have
anything to do with that.

505
00:27:49,047 --> 00:27:50,505
Let's just take a left in here.

506
00:28:03,963 --> 00:28:05,338
Buck, am I in trouble?

507
00:28:08,047 --> 00:28:09,172
Be right back.

508
00:28:10,255 --> 00:28:11,796
Well, maybe I'll just come in with you.

509
00:28:11,797 --> 00:28:14,172
Get some beef jerky or help you out,
or whatever.

510
00:28:15,005 --> 00:28:17,380
That's kind of you, Daniel.
But I'll take care of it.

511
00:28:18,547 --> 00:28:19,630
Just sit tight, yeah?

512
00:28:36,213 --> 00:28:38,463
[breathing nervously]

513
00:28:39,713 --> 00:28:43,672
- [car beeping]
- [exhales]

514
00:28:47,588 --> 00:28:50,338
[thudding]

515
00:28:53,588 --> 00:28:54,755
[nervously] Mmm!

516
00:29:34,755 --> 00:29:35,922
[car door closes]

517
00:29:43,588 --> 00:29:44,922
[Wesley] Long time, pal.

518
00:29:45,922 --> 00:29:47,547
[chuckles] Looking good, Wes.

519
00:29:48,297 --> 00:29:50,755
Fucking hell.
You've come up in the world, haven't you?

520
00:29:51,088 --> 00:29:52,297
Living the dream.

521
00:29:53,213 --> 00:29:55,505
I understand you have
some sort of open assignment.

522
00:29:56,297 --> 00:29:57,797
We're looking to you for...

523
00:29:58,338 --> 00:29:59,505
creativity.

524
00:30:05,088 --> 00:30:07,338
[Buck] Well, you've come to
the right place, then, haven't you?

525
00:30:09,172 --> 00:30:11,672
- [door buzzes]
- [officer] Sign here.

526
00:30:17,588 --> 00:30:18,755
Do you need anything?

527
00:30:21,463 --> 00:30:22,713
What are you gonna do now?

528
00:30:24,630 --> 00:30:25,963
What am I gonna do?

529
00:30:26,838 --> 00:30:29,380
I don't know.
Wait for 'em to come find me.

530
00:30:33,380 --> 00:30:35,255
All right. Good to see you, Fembot.

531
00:30:37,588 --> 00:30:39,422
[door opens]

532
00:30:40,797 --> 00:30:41,921
[groans]

533
00:30:41,922 --> 00:30:44,087
[Daredevil] You recognize this place,
you piece of shit?

534
00:30:44,088 --> 00:30:45,671
[sighs] Fuck.

535
00:30:45,672 --> 00:30:48,172
[panting]

536
00:30:52,672 --> 00:30:55,047
We should be safe here for now.

537
00:30:55,255 --> 00:30:58,130
[chuckles] Safe?

538
00:30:58,963 --> 00:31:00,463
What does that even mean?

539
00:31:02,005 --> 00:31:03,963
You know what happens if she dies?

540
00:31:04,463 --> 00:31:06,922
Fisk turns the city upside-down
and shakes it

541
00:31:07,755 --> 00:31:09,088
until he finds us...

542
00:31:09,797 --> 00:31:11,004
and kills us.

543
00:31:11,005 --> 00:31:12,337
Uh, me.

544
00:31:12,338 --> 00:31:13,754
- Kills me.
- Us.

545
00:31:13,755 --> 00:31:14,755
I was there.

546
00:31:15,505 --> 00:31:17,380
That is more than enough for Fisk.

547
00:31:18,088 --> 00:31:19,088
[knocking on door]

548
00:31:28,505 --> 00:31:29,547
It's open.

549
00:31:34,380 --> 00:31:36,172
What the fuck you doing here, Foggy?

550
00:31:37,880 --> 00:31:39,755
[Daredevil] I know someone who can help.

551
00:31:40,338 --> 00:31:42,004
- A nurse.
- Nurses,

552
00:31:42,005 --> 00:31:43,588
doctors...

553
00:31:44,422 --> 00:31:45,588
lawyers.

554
00:31:46,380 --> 00:31:48,880
Vigilantes, assassins.

555
00:31:49,797 --> 00:31:52,047
Killing people, saving people.

556
00:31:54,672 --> 00:31:56,380
Act like it makes a difference.

557
00:31:58,088 --> 00:31:59,713
Like it matters at all.

558
00:32:01,463 --> 00:32:02,797
[Foggy] I wanted to give you this.

559
00:32:06,047 --> 00:32:07,047
The hell is this?

560
00:32:07,630 --> 00:32:10,672
I was hoping you'd take that,
and, I don't know...

561
00:32:12,130 --> 00:32:13,212
get out of here.

562
00:32:13,213 --> 00:32:14,880
I don't even know where, but...

563
00:32:15,422 --> 00:32:16,962
Wait, wait, wait. So you--

564
00:32:16,963 --> 00:32:18,672
- You gonna give me money?
- No.

565
00:32:19,547 --> 00:32:21,713
Ray, I already gave it to you.

566
00:32:22,380 --> 00:32:25,380
What I want is for you
to start over with it.

567
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:27,588
You got a second chance here.

568
00:32:28,047 --> 00:32:30,338
It's not about them. It's about you.

569
00:32:32,255 --> 00:32:33,255
About me.

570
00:32:35,380 --> 00:32:36,505
Just people...

571
00:32:39,338 --> 00:32:40,338
and, brother...

572
00:32:41,880 --> 00:32:44,379
we are who we are.

573
00:32:44,380 --> 00:32:46,755
[chuckles, coughs]

574
00:32:47,922 --> 00:32:49,213
[Lionel] You know those nights...

575
00:32:50,047 --> 00:32:51,047
we used to, uh...

576
00:32:52,422 --> 00:32:54,755
crash in the living room. Um...

577
00:32:56,422 --> 00:32:57,754
Well, you and Connor

578
00:32:57,755 --> 00:33:00,712
with the, uh, sleeping bags and...
[chuckles]

579
00:33:00,713 --> 00:33:03,213
...uh, the flashlights, you know?

580
00:33:05,797 --> 00:33:08,255
I never really, uh,
had a friend like that.

581
00:33:09,922 --> 00:33:10,922
I know.

582
00:33:14,297 --> 00:33:15,963
[Dex] We're all doing the same thing here.

583
00:33:17,755 --> 00:33:20,630
Acting something out,
scratching some kinda itch.

584
00:33:22,005 --> 00:33:23,297
But the worst part...

585
00:33:25,047 --> 00:33:26,838
is when you think you got it beat.

586
00:33:27,963 --> 00:33:29,047
You think...

587
00:33:30,213 --> 00:33:31,547
"I outran it."

588
00:33:34,505 --> 00:33:36,463
Then you turn the corner, bam...

589
00:33:38,755 --> 00:33:39,838
there it is...

590
00:33:41,588 --> 00:33:43,297
staring you right in the face.

591
00:33:45,797 --> 00:33:47,380
Only it's worse this time.

592
00:33:50,380 --> 00:33:51,422
And, you know...

593
00:33:54,672 --> 00:33:56,463
it was always gonna be there.

594
00:33:57,338 --> 00:33:58,797
[Lionel] Hey, do me a favor, will you?

595
00:33:59,422 --> 00:34:01,380
Tell my brother to stay
right where he's at.

596
00:34:02,838 --> 00:34:05,547
All right? You tell him
I told you to tell him that,

597
00:34:06,088 --> 00:34:08,130
that he ain't got nothing
back here for him.

598
00:34:11,088 --> 00:34:12,172
He's got you.

599
00:34:19,255 --> 00:34:21,255
Come on, Foggy. You gotta go, man.
Get out of here.

600
00:34:25,672 --> 00:34:27,172
[Dex] There's no escaping it.

601
00:34:33,880 --> 00:34:35,422
I'm sorry to interrupt.

602
00:34:35,797 --> 00:34:38,172
This church will always provide shelter

603
00:34:38,838 --> 00:34:40,130
to both of you, but...

604
00:34:41,630 --> 00:34:43,422
I think they know you're here.

605
00:34:44,047 --> 00:34:45,088
[banging on door]

606
00:34:50,005 --> 00:34:51,462
Good evening, officers.
How can I help you?

607
00:34:51,463 --> 00:34:52,754
Hello, Father.

608
00:34:52,755 --> 00:34:55,671
You haven't by chance seen a couple of
vigilantes this fine evening, have you?

609
00:34:55,672 --> 00:34:59,005
I've been in prayers all afternoon,
Officer. I... I don't believe I have.

610
00:35:00,838 --> 00:35:02,588
[Dex groaning]

611
00:35:07,922 --> 00:35:10,213
Listen, we gotta come check the place out.
Mayor's orders.

612
00:35:12,463 --> 00:35:13,463
[Dex] Just...

613
00:35:14,505 --> 00:35:15,588
go.

614
00:35:16,755 --> 00:35:18,047
Don't be an idiot.

615
00:35:18,713 --> 00:35:19,838
Leave me.

616
00:35:20,255 --> 00:35:23,254
Oh, I'm sorry, but weapons are not
permitted in the house of God.

617
00:35:23,255 --> 00:35:24,630
The rules have changed.

618
00:35:25,505 --> 00:35:27,255
Come on in, boys. Sweep it!

619
00:35:28,588 --> 00:35:29,922
[Dex] I killed your friend...

620
00:35:30,297 --> 00:35:31,297
Foggy.

621
00:35:31,755 --> 00:35:33,130
I didn't think twice.

622
00:35:33,630 --> 00:35:35,254
That's who I am.

623
00:35:35,255 --> 00:35:36,880
[man yelling indistinctly]

624
00:35:40,713 --> 00:35:42,130
Just let me die.

625
00:35:44,297 --> 00:35:45,297
I don't...

626
00:35:48,005 --> 00:35:49,504
[Daredevil] Look, I can't save us both.

627
00:35:49,505 --> 00:35:50,922
I'm sorry. I tried.

628
00:35:54,713 --> 00:35:56,379
[choking]

629
00:35:56,380 --> 00:35:58,130
[woman] Let's go! Let's go!

630
00:35:59,422 --> 00:36:02,005
- [siren blaring]
- [man] Sir! Let's go. Move!

631
00:36:04,338 --> 00:36:05,963
[Matt] Imagine my surprise...

632
00:36:07,172 --> 00:36:10,087
when I came back to the office
and found the empty book.

633
00:36:10,088 --> 00:36:11,254
How did you know?

634
00:36:11,255 --> 00:36:14,004
Spend enough time in the same tiny office
with the same person,

635
00:36:14,005 --> 00:36:15,463
you tend to know what they're thinking.

636
00:36:22,130 --> 00:36:23,130
I'm sorry.

637
00:36:25,297 --> 00:36:26,546
I'll pay it back.

638
00:36:26,547 --> 00:36:27,547
[snickers]

639
00:36:30,088 --> 00:36:32,047
Foggy the Fembot. [chuckles]

640
00:36:32,963 --> 00:36:35,504
And there I was thinking
the Murdock and Nelson fund

641
00:36:35,505 --> 00:36:37,338
was supposed to be about the future.

642
00:36:38,380 --> 00:36:39,880
It is, Matt.

643
00:36:41,797 --> 00:36:43,172
But not just ours.

644
00:36:47,963 --> 00:36:48,963
[Matt] So, where to now?

645
00:36:50,047 --> 00:36:51,837
- Josie's.
- Obviously.

646
00:36:51,838 --> 00:36:52,963
What are we celebrating?

647
00:36:55,422 --> 00:36:56,547
Mercy.

648
00:37:15,213 --> 00:37:16,213
Fuck.

649
00:37:18,797 --> 00:37:19,963
Where'd he go?

650
00:37:22,422 --> 00:37:23,463
[birds chirping softly]

651
00:37:38,922 --> 00:37:40,672
You really don't have to do this, man.

652
00:37:43,672 --> 00:37:45,754
I don't even know what I did.
But whatever it was,

653
00:37:45,755 --> 00:37:48,005
it was probably stupid,
and I probably deserve it.

654
00:37:49,088 --> 00:37:50,713
But I could just walk away, man.

655
00:37:51,505 --> 00:37:53,337
I could just disa-fucking-ppear,

656
00:37:53,338 --> 00:37:56,630
and you wouldn't hear anything from me.
Not a peep, not a tweet. Nothing.

657
00:37:58,588 --> 00:38:01,547
Man, I'd be like-- I'd be like Casper.
I mean, I'd be like a ghost.

658
00:38:07,963 --> 00:38:09,463
Look, I didn't fucking leak it.

659
00:38:10,255 --> 00:38:11,255
It wasn't me.

660
00:38:14,588 --> 00:38:15,588
I promise.

661
00:38:17,880 --> 00:38:19,338
Get out of the car, Daniel.

662
00:38:30,505 --> 00:38:31,505
Delivery.

663
00:38:49,588 --> 00:38:50,838
I like you, Daniel.

664
00:38:52,297 --> 00:38:53,422
I really do.

665
00:38:54,505 --> 00:38:56,630
But we work for a man
who can change your life.

666
00:38:58,380 --> 00:38:59,630
Has changed your life.

667
00:39:01,130 --> 00:39:02,630
And all he asks in return...

668
00:39:03,713 --> 00:39:04,713
is loyalty.

669
00:39:06,047 --> 00:39:07,130
Unbridled,

670
00:39:07,838 --> 00:39:09,130
unquestioned...

671
00:39:10,005 --> 00:39:11,672
- loyalty.
- Well, I've been loyal.

672
00:39:12,380 --> 00:39:13,922
I've stayed loyal, Buck.

673
00:39:15,630 --> 00:39:16,838
I'll do anything.

674
00:39:18,088 --> 00:39:21,004
I've said it before.
I'll do whatever it takes.

675
00:39:21,005 --> 00:39:22,088
Please.

676
00:39:23,963 --> 00:39:25,005
Make a choice.

677
00:39:32,297 --> 00:39:33,297
Saw...

678
00:39:33,963 --> 00:39:35,338
or shovel.

679
00:39:36,422 --> 00:39:38,088
[gasps softly]

680
00:39:56,713 --> 00:39:57,880
You know, I was thinking.

681
00:39:59,130 --> 00:40:00,837
Maybe, uh,

682
00:40:00,838 --> 00:40:02,713
instead of Murdock and Nelson,

683
00:40:03,172 --> 00:40:05,797
maybe it's Nelson and Murdock.

684
00:40:06,963 --> 00:40:08,379
- [Foggy] I like that.
- Yeah?

685
00:40:08,380 --> 00:40:09,462
I bumped you up.

686
00:40:09,463 --> 00:40:11,087
- [Foggy] I love that.
- You're goin' up in the world, buddy.

687
00:40:11,088 --> 00:40:12,837
- I am going up in the world.
- [Matt chuckles]

688
00:40:12,838 --> 00:40:15,546
And I think the next 50 rounds are on you.

689
00:40:15,547 --> 00:40:17,587
[Foggy] I don't know about 50.
Fifty sounds a little...

690
00:40:17,588 --> 00:40:19,796
- [Matt] Forty-nine. Sold.
- Forty-seven.

691
00:40:19,797 --> 00:40:21,588
[Daredevil grunting]

692
00:40:42,213 --> 00:40:43,712
Little help?

693
00:40:43,713 --> 00:40:45,130
[sighs in annoyance]

694
00:41:01,297 --> 00:41:03,130
[Vanessa grunts softly]

695
00:41:06,797 --> 00:41:08,130
Vanessa.

696
00:41:08,630 --> 00:41:09,754
You're here.

697
00:41:09,755 --> 00:41:11,338
Yes, I'm here.

698
00:41:12,713 --> 00:41:14,338
I'm right here.

699
00:41:15,338 --> 00:41:16,963
It's so good to see you.

700
00:41:18,088 --> 00:41:20,338
Why are you acting so strange?

701
00:41:21,005 --> 00:41:22,005
Well, I... I...

702
00:41:22,463 --> 00:41:23,588
I didn't think... I...

703
00:41:24,588 --> 00:41:25,672
I didn't think that...

704
00:41:26,297 --> 00:41:28,380
You didn't think what?

705
00:41:32,797 --> 00:41:33,797
I just...

706
00:41:34,172 --> 00:41:35,422
I wasn't... [sobs]

707
00:41:39,255 --> 00:41:41,297
I wasn't sure that I would see you again.

708
00:41:43,547 --> 00:41:45,629
That's absurd. I'm right here.

709
00:41:45,630 --> 00:41:47,338
Yes, of course. Of course you are.

710
00:41:47,630 --> 00:41:49,338
Yes, you are right here. Of course.

711
00:41:54,172 --> 00:41:56,337
What can I do? Can I do something for you?

712
00:41:56,338 --> 00:41:58,796
Are you thirsty?
Can I get you something to drink?

713
00:41:58,797 --> 00:42:00,671
Like water, or...

714
00:42:00,672 --> 00:42:03,212
Or are you hungry?
I can get you something to eat.

715
00:42:03,213 --> 00:42:05,754
Anything. I--
I could get anything you want.

716
00:42:05,755 --> 00:42:06,837
Yes.

717
00:42:06,838 --> 00:42:09,255
I'd like a pineapple juice.

718
00:42:10,088 --> 00:42:11,213
With ice.

719
00:42:13,297 --> 00:42:14,880
You don't like pineapple.

720
00:42:15,380 --> 00:42:16,380
I don't?

721
00:42:16,838 --> 00:42:18,046
No. Your-- Your lips.

722
00:42:18,047 --> 00:42:20,213
It-- It makes them tingle, I believe.

723
00:42:25,172 --> 00:42:26,712
Let's try anyway.

724
00:42:26,713 --> 00:42:27,922
- [Fisk] Mmm-hmm.
- Shall we?

725
00:42:28,338 --> 00:42:29,421
Yeah. Nurse?

726
00:42:29,422 --> 00:42:30,422
Nurse!

727
00:42:30,547 --> 00:42:31,629
[nurse] Is everything okay?

728
00:42:31,630 --> 00:42:33,796
No. I mean, she's awake.

729
00:42:33,797 --> 00:42:36,587
Wait. She wants a pineapple juice.

730
00:42:36,588 --> 00:42:37,921
Sir, I need to--

731
00:42:37,922 --> 00:42:38,922
No!

732
00:42:39,838 --> 00:42:42,547
Pineapple juice in a glass, with ice.

733
00:42:43,713 --> 00:42:46,046
- Wilson.
- Yes?

734
00:42:46,047 --> 00:42:48,129
Why did you scare the poor girl? She--

735
00:42:48,130 --> 00:42:49,212
[Fisk] No.

736
00:42:49,213 --> 00:42:52,172
- You practically made her cry.
- No, I, I just... Um...

737
00:42:52,880 --> 00:42:55,297
I'm just overwhelmed, my love, that's all.

738
00:42:57,005 --> 00:42:58,171
Please.

739
00:42:58,172 --> 00:42:59,672
I've never seen you like this.

740
00:43:00,630 --> 00:43:01,963
I just thought that...

741
00:43:04,338 --> 00:43:06,754
I'm just glad you're with me here again.

742
00:43:06,755 --> 00:43:07,755
That's all.

743
00:43:08,713 --> 00:43:09,796
[Vanessa] But...

744
00:43:09,797 --> 00:43:11,547
why did you think I'd gone?

745
00:43:12,005 --> 00:43:13,005
I don't know.

746
00:43:14,338 --> 00:43:15,338
I, uh...

747
00:43:17,088 --> 00:43:18,922
I just missed you so much.

748
00:43:19,380 --> 00:43:21,462
That's all. I just missed you so much.

749
00:43:21,463 --> 00:43:22,921
I missed you, too.

750
00:43:22,922 --> 00:43:25,922
- Yeah?
- I'm so glad to be here with you.

751
00:43:30,047 --> 00:43:31,047
Yes, baby.

752
00:43:43,880 --> 00:43:46,047
Is there something else you need, my dear?

753
00:43:46,922 --> 00:43:47,922
No.

754
00:43:49,422 --> 00:43:50,755
That was divine.

755
00:43:51,422 --> 00:43:52,422
Good.

756
00:43:55,672 --> 00:43:56,672
[Vanessa] Wilson.

757
00:43:57,255 --> 00:43:58,587
Yes, my love.

758
00:43:58,588 --> 00:44:00,172
Will you tell me a story?

759
00:44:02,255 --> 00:44:03,380
A story?

760
00:44:05,047 --> 00:44:06,379
Yes.

761
00:44:06,380 --> 00:44:08,588
A story, please.

762
00:44:10,047 --> 00:44:12,297
What kind of story
would you like me to tell?

763
00:44:13,297 --> 00:44:15,422
Tell me the story of how we met.

764
00:44:17,713 --> 00:44:19,213
Oh.

765
00:44:26,255 --> 00:44:28,963
I've arranged for a more private
showing, but...

766
00:44:29,838 --> 00:44:30,838
this is it.

767
00:44:31,255 --> 00:44:32,422
This is the gallery.

768
00:44:36,172 --> 00:44:39,629
[Vanessa] Somehow, I must have known
that you would walk

769
00:44:39,630 --> 00:44:42,005
through those doors and change everything.

770
00:44:43,338 --> 00:44:45,130
Lucky then, I guess, that day.

771
00:44:45,755 --> 00:44:47,547
Mmm, no.

772
00:44:48,172 --> 00:44:49,172
Not luck.

773
00:44:50,630 --> 00:44:51,755
Not luck at all.

774
00:44:53,547 --> 00:44:55,879
It was the grand design.

775
00:44:55,880 --> 00:44:57,755
- Mmm.
- [Vanessa chuckles]

